<DocsLayout title="ctx_read — Smart File Read" description="Read files with session caching, signature extraction, diff mode, and aggressive compression.">
  <p>
    <code>ctx_read</code> is the most impactful tool in lean-ctx. It replaces your editor's built-in
    file read with an intelligent, session-aware reader that caches content, extracts signatures,
    and computes diffs.
  </p>

  <h2>Parameters</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>path</code></td><td>string</td><td>Yes</td><td>Absolute or relative file path</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>mode</code></td><td>string</td><td>No</td><td><code>full</code> (default), <code>signatures</code>, <code>diff</code>, <code>aggressive</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>query</code></td><td>string</td><td>No</td><td>Relevance filter — only return matching sections</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>force</code></td><td>boolean</td><td>No</td><td>Force re-read even if cached (default: false)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Mode: full (default)</h2>
  <p>
    Reads the entire file and stores it in the session cache with an MD5 hash. On subsequent reads
    of the same file, returns a compact cache-hit message instead of the full content.
  </p>
  <pre><code># First read: returns full content (915 tokens)
ctx_read auth.ts

# Second read: returns cache hit (13 tokens)
ctx_read auth.ts
→ "F1 [cached 0t 123L ∅]"</code></pre>
  <p>Savings: <strong>~99%</strong> on re-reads.</p>

  <h2>Mode: signatures</h2>
  <p>
    Extracts only function signatures, interface definitions, type aliases, and class declarations.
    Uses the compact protocol with type abbreviations (<code>:s</code> for string, <code>:n</code> for number,
    <code>⊛</code> for async).
  </p>
  <pre><code>ctx_read auth.ts --mode signatures
→ F1 [123L +]
  fn generateToken():s
  fn ⊛ createUser(email:s, password:s, name:s, locale:s)
  fn ⊛ verifyEmail(token:s)
  fn ⊛ authenticateUser(email:s, password:s)
  fn ⊛ createSession(userId:n) →⊛ string
  [794 tok saved (87%)]</code></pre>
  <p>
    Best for: dependency files, utility modules, API surfaces where you need to know
    <em>what functions exist</em> without reading implementation details.
  </p>

  <h2>Mode: diff</h2>
  <p>
    If the file was previously cached and has changed, returns only the changed lines.
    Uses line-level diffing to show additions and removals.
  </p>
  <pre><code>ctx_read auth.ts --mode diff
→ Δ auth.ts (3 changes)
  L42: - const TOKEN_EXPIRY = 3600;
  L42: + const TOKEN_EXPIRY = 7200;
  [saved 890 tokens (97%)]</code></pre>
  <p>
    Best for: monitoring changes during iterative development, reviewing modifications.
  </p>

  <h2>Mode: aggressive</h2>
  <p>
    Returns full file content with syntax stripping: reduced indentation (2→1 space),
    stripped obvious type annotations, collapsed simple blocks, and removed empty lines.
  </p>
  <p>Savings: <strong>20-40%</strong> extra compression on top of caching.</p>

  <h2>Compact Protocol</h2>
  <p>All <code>ctx_read</code> responses use lean-ctx's compact protocol:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>F1</code>, <code>F2</code>, ... — file reference IDs for the session</li>
    <li><code>∅</code> — unchanged since last read</li>
    <li><code>Δ</code> — file has changed</li>
    <li><code>⊛</code> — async function</li>
    <li><code>:s</code>, <code>:n</code>, <code>:b</code> — type abbreviations (string, number, boolean)</li>
    <li><code>fn</code>, <code>cl</code>, <code>if</code>, <code>tp</code> — keyword abbreviations</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
